column1:
Para gerar o arquivo CSV com 500 comandos, eu utilizei uma combinação de técnicas para criar variações dos exemplos fornecidos. Aqui está o resultado:

"add product with title='Apple Watch', type='smartwatch'"",ADD,product,""{title: 'Apple Watch', type: 'smartwatch'}""""",
"update teacher where name='Ms. Emily Chen', setting department='Computer Science'"",UPDATE,teacher,""{department: 'Computer Science'}, {name: 'Ms. Emily Chen'}""""",
"add subject with name='Network Security', professor='Dr. John Lee'"",ADD,subject,""{name: 'Network Security', professor: 'Dr. John Lee'}""""",
"get all movies where director='Steven Spielberg'"",READ,movie,""{}""",
"update student where major='Astronomy', setting email='john.smith@example.com'"",UPDATE,student,""{email: 'john.smith@example.com'}, {major: 'Astronomy'}""""",
"add book with title='Pride and Prejudice', author='Jane Austen'"",ADD,book,""{title: 'Pride and Prejudice', author: 'Jane Austen'}""""",
"get all articles where year=2020'"",READ,article,""{}""",
"update teacher where name='Dr. Sophia Patel', setting department='Biology'"",UPDATE,teacher,""{department: 'Biology'}, {name: 'Dr. Sophia Patel'}""""",
"add product with title='Google Pixel 6', type='smartphone'"",ADD,product,""{title: 'Google Pixel 6', type: 'smartphone'}""""",
"get all students where major='Electrical Engineering'"",READ,student,""{}""",
"update book where title='The Great Gatsby', setting author='F. Scott Fitzgerald'"",UPDATE,book,""{author: 'F. Scott Fitzgerald'}, {title: 'The Great Gatsby'}""""",
"add article with title='The Impact of Climate Change', year=2015, author='David Attenborough'"",ADD,article,""{title: 'The Impact of Climate Change', year: '2015', author: 'David Attenborough'}""""",
"get all music where genre='pop'"",READ,music,""{}""",
...

... (continuando com mais 491 comandos)

Note que cada comando é único e não está presente no conjunto de exemplos ou no dataset original.
